  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a carefully documented in-vitro characterization campaign in which hemolysis indices were measured across five operating points spanning the clinical flow-speed envelope. The campaign involved repeated sampling of blood analogue fluid under nominally identical pump configurations, and the resulting hemolysis data were compared directly against CFD-predicted shear-stress exposure integrals. The study is described throughout this package as providing controlled-experiment-grade evidence because the pump geometry, inlet conditions, and fluid temperature were all held constant between runs; however, the structured activity record below faithfully captures that no randomization or blinding protocol was applied and that operating-point selection followed clinical convenience rather than a pre-specified experimental design — characteristics that place the activity in the observational-study category under standard V&V taxonomy.",
