      "name": "Relative hemolysis index comparison — CFD vs. in-vitro measurements",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis indices (RH) at five flow-speed operating points were compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements collected during the pump characterization campaign. Across all five operating points the predicted RH values fell within 12% of measured values, and in all cases RH < 1 relative to the predicate device. The activity generating this result is the in-vitro pump characterization study, which the narrative team characterizes as a controlled in-vitro experiment because pump geometry and boundary conditions were held fixed. Agreement between prediction and measurement at all five operating points is taken as confirmation that the CFD model correctly identifies worst-case hemolysis conditions.",
