        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/pump-characterization-study",
        "type": "Activity",
        "name": "In-vitro pump hemolysis characterization study",
        "description": "Blood analogue fluid (porcine red blood cells in phosphate-buffered saline) was circulated through the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump at five clinically representative flow-speed combinations. Hemolysis was quantified via plasma-free haemoglobin measurement at 30-minute intervals over a 6-hour run. Operating points were selected based on clinical convenience sampling of the device's operating envelope rather than a pre-specified randomized design; no blinding or randomization protocol was applied. Pump geometry and inlet temperature were held nominally constant across runs but were not independently varied or controlled as experimental factors. The data were subsequently used to compute normalized index of haemolysis (NIH) and relative haemolysis index (RH) values for comparison with CFD output.",
        "activityType": "observational-study"
      }
