      "description": "For MRL 2 hemolysis CFD models used in Class II device submissions, the primary validation activity supporting the Output Comparison credibility factor shall employ a controlled-experiment methodology in which at least one independent variable is systematically varied under pre-specified conditions with appropriate controls, enabling causal inference between model inputs and measured hemolysis outputs. Observational or convenience-sampled datasets do not satisfy this requirement because they do not support the causal inference chain required to confirm that the CFD model correctly predicts hemolysis sensitivity to operating-condition variation.",
